        <heading>Nursing Home Financial Assistance</heading>
        <section eId="sec_17a_811">
          <num>17a-811</num>
          <heading>(Formerly Sec. 10-294a). Legal blindness. Impaired vision. Defined</heading>
          <subsection eId="17a_811__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A person is legally blind if such person's central visual acuity does not exceed 20/200 in the better eye with correcting lenses, or if such person's visual acuity is greater than 20/200 but is accompanied by a limitation in the fields of vision such that the widest diameter of the visual field subtends an angle no greater than twenty degrees;</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="17a_811__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A person has impaired vision if such person's central visual acuity does not exceed 20/70 in the better eye with correcting lenses.
(Return to ChapterTable of Contents)(Return toList of Chapters)(Return toList of Titles)</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
      </chapter>
